Excavations revealed that the area had been used for farming, resulting in the removal of some chamber stones.

According to the late {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}} text ''{{ill|Shinpen Musashi Fudoki Ko|ja|新編武蔵風土記稿|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'', “40–50 Kofuns existed during the Genroku era but had decreased to 14–15 mounds by the late Edo period.”{{sfn|Shinpen Musashi Fudoki Ko}} The area is largely uninvestigated, and further surveys could reveal more Kofuns. However, the construction of residential buildings in the area is expected to affect future investigations.

Nearby sites include {{ill|Inarizuka Kofun|ja|稲荷塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}}<ref name=Tama>{{Cite web|和書|author=Tama City Board of Education|url=http://www.city.tama.lg.jp/0000003429.html|title=Tama City's Cultural Properties (Inarizuka Kofun)|work=Tama City|accessdate=2020-09-22}}</ref>, {{ill|Usuizuka Kofun|ja|臼井塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kōshintzuka Kofun|ja|庚申塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and across the {{ill|Ōkurigawa River|ja|大栗川|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the {{ill|Nakawada Cave Tomb Cluster|ja|中和田横穴墓群|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and the {{ill|Manzoin-dai Kofun Cluster|ja|万蔵院台古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Hino City|ja|日野市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Numerous artifacts from the Kofun period, including residential site remains and pottery, have also been found in the area. It is considered one of the most prominent kofun clusters in Tokyo.

The historical museum at {{ill|Parthenon Tama|ja|パルテノン多摩|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, near {{ill|Tama-Center Station|ja|多摩センター駅|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, displays panels on the Tsukahara Kofun Cluster and exhibits artifacts, including iron arrowheads, small swords, metal rings, Sue pottery, Haji pottery, and a reconstructed {{ill|Tachi sword|ja|大刀|qq=draft|qq=draft}} model from Mound 5.

== Excavation Details for Each Mound ==
=== Mound No. 1 ===
A circular Kofun with a diameter of 9 meters and a height of 2 meters. It is the only mound in the cluster with a remaining mound. Uninvestigated to date, stones thought to be pillar stones for the {{ill|burial chamber|ja|羨道|1=endō|lt=endō (tomb entrance)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} entrance are visible.

=== Mound No. 2 ===
A circular Kofun with an estimated diameter of 19 meters and a surrounding ditch of 25 meters. Constructed in the late 6th century. Two additional burial pits, likely for secondary burials, were found. A late 6th-century Haji pottery jar was unearthed from the ditch.

=== Mound No. 3 ===
A circular Kofun with an estimated diameter of 10 meters, featuring double surrounding ditches on the eastern side. Dated to the mid-6th century.

=== Mound No. 4 ===
A circular Kofun with an estimated diameter of 14 meters. Constructed in the early 7th century, it has a semi-underground horizontal stone chamber with a single, slightly curved structure. Artifacts include three swords, numerous iron arrowheads, metal earrings, a pair of bronze armlets, and various beads. Artifacts are stored at {{ill|Tamagawa University|ja|玉川大学|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

=== Mound No. 5 ===
A circular Kofun with an estimated diameter of 14 meters. Constructed in the late 6th century (575–600). It features a stone chamber with a passage and a rectangular chamber. excavations include three long swords, one short sword, four knives, approximately 70 arrowheads, Haji pottery, and Sue pottery.

=== Mound No. 6 ===
A circular Kofun with an estimated diameter of 18 meters. Built in the early 7th century, it features a stone chamber with a double-curved structure. Artifacts include an iron sword, a knife, and two gold-plated copper earrings.

=== Mound No. 7 ===
Only stone chamber remnants were found. The Kofun and ditch were not confirmed.

=== Mound No. 8 ===
A probable circular Kofun with a diameter of 14 meters, built in the late 6th century (575–600). Partial ditches and Sue pottery imitations were found.

=== Mound No. 9 ===
A burial chamber with a single-sided structure was found. Neither the Kofun nor the ditch was confirmed. Dated to the mid-7th century.

=== Mound No. 10 ===
A probable circular Kofun with an estimated diameter of 18 meters. A partially confirmed ditch surrounds it.

